                <h1>Understanding Wetlands: Importance & Ecosystem Services</h1>
                <p>Wetlands are vital ecosystems characterized by saturated soils, standing water, and diverse plant life. They serve as natural water filters, protect against floods, and provide habitats for numerous species. Covering about 6% of Earth's surface, wetlands play a crucial role in maintaining biodiversity and supporting local communities.</p>
